==English==
===Intransitive verb===
'''crawl'''
#To [[creep]]; to move slowly on [[hand]]s and [[knee]]s, or by [[drag]]ging the [[body]] along the [[ground]]
#To move forward slowly, with [[frequent]] stops.
#To act in a [[servile]] manner
#To [[teem]]; to seem as if covered with moving things
#:''The crime scene was '''crawl'''ing with police and reporters.
#:''The horrible sight made my skin '''crawl'''. 
#To [[swim]] using the crawl [[stroke]]

===Noun===
'''crawl'''
#The act of moving slowly on hands and knees etc, or with frequent stops
#A [[rapid]] swimming stroke with [[alternate]] [[overarm]] strokes and a [[flutter]]ing [[kick]]

